{
  "hooks": {
    "SessionStart": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/session-start.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Write|Edit",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/pre-tool-use.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Write|Edit",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/post-tool-use.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "Stop": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "prompt",
            "prompt": "Review your last response and check for signals that require follow-up. Respond ONLY with valid JSON: {\"ok\": true} if no signals found, or {\"ok\": false, \"reason\": \"<signals>\"} if signals are present.\n\nCheck these three categories:\n\n(1) ARCHITECTURE/PRODUCT SIGNALS — significant technical choice with trade-offs (database, architectural pattern, API design, infra decision); hard constraint that must NEVER be violated (data integrity, security boundary, domain purity); or clearly defined new feature with enough detail to act on. Signal text: '💡 ADR candidate — run /keel:adr to capture it.' OR '💡 Invariant candidate — run /keel:invariant to capture it.' OR '💡 PRD candidate — run /keel:prd to capture it.'\n\n(2) DOC GAP SIGNALS — new HTTP route or API endpoint; new env var or config key; new CLI flag or command; new infra component (Docker service, queue, cron, external dep); breaking change to existing API. Signal text: '📄 Doc gap: {specific thing} may need docs — run /keel:docs to review.' Do NOT flag internal refactors, bug fixes, test changes, or formatting.\n\n(3) SECURITY SIGNALS — authentication, authorization, payment processing, PII handling, cryptography, token management, or access control was central to the response. Signal text: '🔒 Security-sensitive domain — run /keel:audit before shipping.'\n\nOnly surface a signal when clearly present. If multiple signals, combine them in the reason field separated by newlines. If no signals, respond with {\"ok\": true}."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PreCompact": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$HOME/.keel/hooks/pre-compact.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
